he effective annualised rate payable by the Borrower based on an all-inclusive cost and margin including cost of funds, credit cost and operating cost, processing fee, verification charges, maintenance charges, etc., and / or such specific costs indicated in the KFS.\n2. **APPLICATION FORM:** means, direct application made by the Borrower for the Loan through web portal / mobile application of the Lender.\n3. **BORROWER:** means the individual availing the Loan from the Lender in under these Terms hereof and who has agreed to the terms and conditions contained in these Terms for the purpose of availing Loan.\n4. **BULLET REPAYMENT:** shall mean such Loan product where the Borrower repays the full Outstanding Amount on one fixed Due Date.\n5. **COMMERCIAL TERMS:** shall mean the terms applicable to the Loan as detailed in SCHEDULE I of these Terms.\n6. **DUE DATE:** shall mean such date identified in the Commercial Terms and KFS on which the EMI shall be due and payable by the Borrower.\n7. **ECS OR NACH:** means electronic clearing services / electronic payment services, consented to in writing by Borrower, for facilitating the payment of EMI, fees and other applicable charges to the Lender in connection with the Loan.\n8. **ESSENTIAL DATA:** means such data which is statutorily required by the Lender to be retained for compliance with applicable laws.\n9. **EQUATED MONTHLY INSTALLMENT (EMI) / INSTALLMENT:** shall mean such Loan product whereby the Borrower repays the Outstanding Amount at such frequency (monthly / quarterly) as indicated in the Commercial Terms on the respective Due Date during the Tenure of the Loan.\n10. **GRIEVANCE REDRESSAL OFFICER:** shall mean the officer named in the Commercial Terms and KFS who shall address and resolve the complaints / queries of Borrowers.\n11. **LOAN:** means the credit facility granted / agreed to be granted by the Lender to the Borrower.\n12. **KFS:** shall mean the Key Fact Statement provided by the Lender before the execution of these Terms which lays down details such as Annual Percentage Rate, terms and conditions of recovery mechanism, details of Grievance Redressal Officer, and Cooling-off/ Look-up period.\n13. **OUTSTANDING AMOUNT:** shall mean all amounts pertaining to the Loan whether by way of the principal amount together with any EMI, accrued interest, default interest, Prepayment charges, bounce charges and/or any other cost and charges indicated herein or the Commercial Terms or KFS.\n14. **PREPAYMENT:** means premature repayment of the Loan in full, including principal amount, interest thereon, and all Outstanding Amount which is not yet due for payment by the Borrower under the Terms.\n15. **REPAYMENT SCHEDULE:** shall mean the schedule shared by the Lender which indicates the Outstanding Amount and the Due Date on which the said Outstanding Amount is to be repaid by the Borrower.\n16. **REPAYMENT INSTRUMENT:** shall mean an ECS / NACH / standing instructions / cheque / post-dated cheque (PDC) and / or such other negotiable instrument or mode of payment that may be notified by the RBI from time to time.\n17. **RBI:** shall mean the Reserve Bank of India.\n18. **TENURE:** shall mean the months / years as indicated in the Commercial Terms and KFS.\n\n**Borrower's Representations, Warranties and Undertakings:**\n\nThe Borrower hereby represents and warrants as follows:\n\n1. Is of sound mind, competent to contract, has attained the age of majority, and capable of fulfilling the obligations under these terms;\n2. Is financially stable, not declared bankrupt or insolvent, and capable of repaying the Loan.", "content_chunks": ["India (\"Lender\"), under the conditions specified herein.\n\nThe Borrower hereby understands and acknowledges that these Terms are for two loan products, namely (a) Bullet Repayment; (b) EMI / Installment and that based on the nature / type of Loan availed by me / us through the Application Form and thereafter accepted in the KFS, only the respective Loan product Terms shall apply.\n\n**Definition:**\n\nIn these Terms, the capitalized words shall have the following meanings. All terms capitalized but not defined below shall have such meaning as ascribed to them in the Commercial Terms:\n\n1. **ANNUALISED PERCENTAGE RATE / APR:** means the effective annualised rate payable by the Borrower based on an all-inclusive cost and margin including cost of funds, credit cost and operating cost, processing fee, verification charges, maintenance charges, etc., and / or such specific costs indicated in the KFS.\n2. **APPLICATION FORM:** means, direct application made by the Borrower for the Loan through web portal / mobile application of the Lender.\n3. **BORROWER:** means the individual availing the Loan from the Lender in under these Terms hereof and who has agreed to the terms and conditions contained in these Terms for the purpose of availing Loan.\n4. **BULLET REPAYMENT:** shall mean such Loan product where the Borrower repays the full Outstanding Amount on one fixed Due Date.\n5. **COMMERCIAL TERMS:** shall mean the terms applicable to the Loan as detailed in SCHEDULE I of these Terms.\n6. **DUE DATE:** shall mean such date identified in the Commercial Terms and KFS on which the EMI shall be due and payable by the Borrower.\n7. **ECS OR NACH:** means electronic clearing services / electronic payment services, consented to in writing by Borrower, for facilitating the payment of EMI, fees and other applicable charges to the Lender in connection with the Loan.\n8. **ESSENTIAL DATA:** means such data which is statutorily required by the Lender to be retained for compliance with applicable laws.\n9. **EQUATED MONTHLY INSTALLMENT (EMI) / INSTALLMENT:** shall mean such Loan product whereby the Borrower repays the Outstanding Amount at such frequency (monthly / quarterly) as indicated in the Commercial Terms on the respective Due Date during the Tenure of the Loan.\n10. **GRIEVANCE REDRESSAL OFFICER:** shall mean the officer named in the Commercial Terms and KFS who shall address and resolve the complaints / queries of Borrowers.\n11. **LOAN:** means the credit facility granted / agreed to be granted by the Lender to the Borrower.\n12. **KFS:** shall mean the Key Fact Statement provided by the Lender before the execution of these Terms which lays down details such as Annual Percentage Rate, terms and conditions of recovery mechanism, details of Grievance Redressal Officer, and Cooling-off/ Look-up period.\n13. **OUTSTANDING AMOUNT:** shall mean all amounts pertaining to the Loan whether by way of the principal amount together with any EMI, accrued interest, default interest, Prepayment charges, bounce charges and/or any other cost and charges indicated herein or the Commercial Terms or KFS.\n14. **PREPAYMENT:** means premature repayment of the Loan in full, including principal amount, interest thereon, and all Outstanding Amount which is not yet due for payment by the Borrower under the Terms.\n15. **REPAYMENT SCHEDULE:** shall mean the schedule shared by the Lender which indicates the Outstanding Amount and the Due Date on which the said Outstanding Amount is to be repaid by the Borrower.\n16. **REPAYMENT INSTRUMENT:** shall mean an ECS / NACH / standing instructions / cheque / post-dated cheque (PDC) and / or such other negotiable instrument or mode of payment that may be notified by the RBI from time to time.\n17. **RBI:** shall mean the Reserve Bank of India.\n18. **TENURE:** shall mean the months / years as indicated in the Commercial Terms and KFS.\n\n**Borrower's Representations, Warranties and Undertakings:**\n\nThe Borrower hereby represents and warrants as follows:\n\n1. Is of sound mind, competent to contract, has attained the age of majority, and capable of fulfilling the obligations under these terms;\n2. Is financially stable, not declared bankrupt or insolvent, and capable of repaying the Loan."], "entities": ["Lender", "Borrower", "KFS", "EMI", "APR", "ECS", "NACH",